Furthermore, the paper's use of a routing-by-agreement algorithm suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), which often involves developing algorithms that can learn and reason about complex data. 

The paper's focus on improving the expressiveness of multi-head attention suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which involves developing neural network models that can learn and adapt to complex data. 

Finally, the paper's mention of machine translation tasks suggests that it may also belong to the sub-category of cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition), which often involves developing models that can process and understand visual data, including text.
